# Bliss Recruitment API

Bliss Recruitment API is a simple API allowing consumers to view polls and vote in them.

## Health Status [/health]

### Get Health Status [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "status": "OK"
        }
        
+ Response 503 (application/json)

        {
            "status": "Service Unavailable. Please try again later."
        }


## Questions Collection [/questions]

### List All Questions [GET /questions?limit={limit}&offset={offset}&filter={filter}]

+ Parameters
    + limit (required, number) ... the number of records to retrieve
    + offset (required, number) ... 0 based starting index of the first retrieved record. If you invoked with limit=5 then you should use offset=5 to obtain the next records. If you asked for 5 but only got 4, e.g., that means there are no more records to show.
    + filter (optional, string) ... use this field to search for the filter pattern on "question" and "choice" properties. The search will perform a "lowercase contains" strategy on those fields to retrieve results.

